íŸ@8f20a35b2ffbe4c2624b2c77e3d72da8faf9b2b41d6bd6bbcb31838e15300462⁄?Title: title: watch
Path: Flags
Content:
``--debounce, -d {duration}``
: Debounce changes for this duration (default: 100ms). Adjust if you find that single writes are reported as multiple events.
``--glob, -g {string}``
: Only report changes for files that match this glob pattern (default: all files)
``--recursive, -r {bool}``
: Watch all directories under 
``<path>``
 recursively. Will be ignored if 
``<path>``
 is a file (default: true).
``--quiet, -q``
: Hide the initial status message (default: false).
``--verbose, -v``
: Operate in verbose mode (default: false).
íŸ@976f018ce7f002d5dfd69dfbeb8556095dae180838340ed5e4e6f03c3e8ea266⁄Title: title: watch
Path: Parameters
Content:
``path``
: The path to watch. Can be a file or directory.
``closure``
: Some Nu code to run whenever a file changes. The closure will be passed 
``operation``
, 
``path``
, and 
``new_path``
 (for renames only) arguments in that order.
