íŸ@27cec12bde3f6689e032d4065cd8b9e370d7227cd153876e30ec41ee4e79df28⁄®Title: title: watch
Path: Examples
Content:
Run 
``cargo test``
 whenever a Rust file changes.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> watch . --glob=**/*.rs {|| cargo test }


```
Watch all changes in the current directory.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> watch . { |op, path, new_path| $"($op) ($path) ($new_path)"}


```
``watch``
 (when run without a closure) can also emit a stream of events it detects.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> watch /foo/bar
    | where operation == Create
    | first 5
    | each {|e| $"New file!: ($e.path)" }
    | to text
    | save --append changes_in_bar.log


```
Print file changes with a debounce time of 5 minutes.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> watch /foo/bar --debounce 5min { |op, path| $"Registered ($op) on ($path)" | print }


```
Note: if you are looking to run a command every N units of time, this can be accomplished with a loop and sleep.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> loop { command; sleep duration }


```
íŸ@2400adff2cdecb3e7fd3f297b7b181b16e3e5c1029c2ef899845cd6a892a0552ŸuTitle: title: watch
